Build a Mortgage Cal

Collecting data on the amount of loan a customer wants to collect : Principal, Annual Interest Rate, Period and Mortgage payment
M=P{\frac  {r(1+r)^{{n}}}{(1+r)^{{n}}-1}}. These variables represent the following inputs:
M is your monthly payment.
P is your principal.
r is your monthly interest rate, calculated by dividing your annual interest rate by 12.
n is your number of payments (the number of months you will be paying the loan)

